Bellair police are appealing for any information following a hit and run in which a 58-year-old man died in Hillary on 11 May. Communications officer Sergeant. M Pillay said: “According to witnesses there was an altercation between the victim and the occupants of a vehicle involved, in Sarnia Rd. “The victim got off his vehicle to approach the driver of the other vehicle. The driver of the white convertible 135i BMW with a black top and GP registration then sped off, turned the vehicle and drove in the direction of the victim, colliding into him. It is a suspected case of road-rage,” said Pillay. Anyone with any info should contact Warrant Officer Ebrahim on 031 451 2824 or Capt Khumalo on 031 451 2819.a